   The following portions of rdprrap are derived from, ported from, or
   closely mirror behavior of stascorp/rdpwrap.  Source comments in
   each file name the specific upstream Delphi source file or block
   they relate to.

   RDPCheck.exe → `rdprrap-check`
     - crates/rdprrap-check/src/disc_reason.rs
         Disconnect-reason code → text table. Structurally ported from
         the `case DiscReason of` block in rdpwrap's RDPCheck source
         (upstream: `src-rdpcheck/MainUnit.pas`).  The displayed text
         strings themselves are from Microsoft's public MSTSCAX
         ExtendedDisconnectReasonCode documentation and are included
         under that public documentation grant, not under Apache-2.0.
     - crates/rdprrap-check/src/main.rs
         `rdprrap-check` is a Rust rewrite of rdpwrap's RDPCheck.exe.
     - crates/rdprrap-check/src/gui.rs
         Window layout intentionally mirrors the essentials of the
         original 640x480 Delphi VCL form (`src-rdpcheck/MainUnit.dfm`),
         minus the embedded MSTSCAX control.
     - crates/rdprrap-check/src/rdp.rs
         Loopback address `127.0.0.2` reuse follows rdpwrap's choice.

   RDPConf.exe → `rdprrap-conf`
     - crates/rdprrap-conf/src/main.rs
         `rdprrap-conf` is a Rust replacement for the Delphi
         `RDPConf.exe` (upstream `src-rdpconfig/`).
     - crates/rdprrap-conf/src/gui.rs
         Two-column layout, live-diagnostics timer, and control
         grouping all mirror the original `RDPConf.exe` window; we
         poll every 1 s instead of upstream's 250 ms.
     - crates/rdprrap-conf/src/registry.rs
         `Shadow` dual-write policy mirrors upstream — the original
         `RDPConf` writes both locations.
     - crates/rdprrap-conf/src/settings.rs
         `ReadSettings` / `WriteSettings` behavior mirrors
         `RDPConf.exe`'s registry I/O.
     - crates/rdprrap-conf/src/diag.rs
         `WrapperState::InstalledRdpWrap` detection recognises an
         existing `rdpwrap.dll` ServiceDll deployment for display.

   RDPWInst.exe → `rdprrap-installer`
     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/main.rs
         Replicates the high-level flow of the Delphi `RDPWInst.exe`
         (upstream `src-installer/RDPWInst.dpr`).
     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/cli.rs
         Default "install on no subcommand" behavior matches
         `RDPWInst.exe`'s flag-style defaults.
     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/install.rs
         Install directory, ServiceDll rewrite, fDenyTSConnections
         handling, AllowMultipleTSSessions handling.  The TS AddIns
         block (`contract::reg::ADDINS_*`) behaviorally mirrors
         `RDPWInst.dpr` lines 982..1022 verbatim (the three subkey
         Name / Type values — no Delphi source text was copied).
     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/service.rs
         netsvcs cohort-service restart mirrors `RDPWInst.dpr`'s
         "shut the whole svchost group" logic (adapted to
         `EnumServicesStatusExW`).
     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/firewall.rs
         Rule names / port / shape follow `RDPWInst.dpr`'s netsh
         invocations (TCP + UDP on 3389, locale-safe naming).
     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/contract.rs
         AddIns Name/Type constants match `RDPWInst.dpr` (the
         `Type = -1 signed` sentinel for Dynamic VC is preserved
         as `0xFFFFFFFF` per Windows REG_DWORD wire format).
     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/version.rs
         CheckTermsrvVersion preflight warns on builds outside the
         set upstream `RDPWInst.dpr` is known to patch.

